The paper presents a set of continuous control tasks with a standardised structure and interpretable rewards, intended to serve as performance benchmarks for reinforcement learning agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The tasks are powered by the MuJoCo physics engine, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper includes benchmarks for several learning algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
